Matrix Guide
1
Open your browser and navigate to: "https://IP_Data_Collector/". You can also use
the a4conf icon on the Data Collector desktop.
2
Click on "Fast-Data" within the main menu.
Made with Scribe - https://scribehow.com 2
3
Select the "Fast Data Matrix service disabled" checkbox to enable the Fast Data
Matrix service.
4
Select "Matrix".
Made with Scribe - https://scribehow.com 3
5
Open the "Matrix ID elements" drop-down menu to show all the Matrix IDs.
6
Select the Matrix ID you want to delete.
Made with Scribe - https://scribehow.com 4
7
Click the "Delete" button to complete the operation.
8
Within this JSON interface of all the Matrix configurations, you can manually edit
Matrix configurations by clicking on the text. Click on the "" icon to expand the
desired section.
Made with Scribe - https://scribehow.com 5
9
Click the "Save" button to save the new configurations.
10
Move to "Manage Iot Gateways".
Made with Scribe - https://scribehow.com 6
11
You can select the checkbox to enable/disable the desired IoT Gateway.
12
Click the "Refresh" button to update the IoT Gateway information table list.
Made with Scribe - https://scribehow.com 7
13
Click on the "Apply" button to apply the new configurations.
14
Select the required option from "Matrix service commands" to start, stop or
restart the Matrix service.
Made with Scribe - https://scribehow.com 8
15
Select "Matrix service status" to disable the Matrix service. After this operation you
will be directed to the "Fast-Data" page.
16
Select the "Reboot Data Sender" checkbox to reboot the Data Sender. Click the
"Apply" button to start the reboot.
